{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab6fd694-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9375"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9375"},"text":"§ 9375.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Production of supplies and munitions: hours and pay of laborers and mechanics","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"During a national emergency declared by the President, the regular working hours of laborers and mechanics of the Department of the Air Force producing military supplies or munitions are 8 hours a day or 40 hours a week. However, under regulations prescribed by the Secretary of the Air Force these hours may be exceeded. Each laborer or mechanic who works more than 40 hours in a workweek shall be paid at a rate not less than one and one-half times the regular hourly rate for each hour in excess of 40.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab6fd695-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/558"},"text":"70A Stat. 558","children":[],"tail":", § 9025; renumbered § 9375, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s806/b/16"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 806(b)(16)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1833"},"text":"132 Stat. 1833","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab6fd696-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab6fd697-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idab6fd6